Design.Component.Label: Naikoon Park
Field.Observer.Name: Lucy Stefanyk
Survey.Observation.Note: Egg >100.  Water level guage installed. .36 (36 cm); water temp warm at surface for about 2' and then cold; pacific chorus egg sacks visible with some (approx 6) that had advanced stages of egg development or very early hatchling phase. Most egg sacks were still in egg form.  No red-legged egg sacks noted. Heavy algae patches and strands covering the wetland; scattered cloud cover < 50%; light breeze; calls in the morning, but none at the time of the survey. 2 Sandhill cranes were in the wetland the entire time of the survey - suspected nest in nearby area. 4 pairs of mallards and one red-tailed hawk observed; calling moise of the Virgina rail present.

Field.Observer.Name: Lucy Stefanyk
Survey.Observation.Note: Count not given.  Scattered cloud >50%; gentle breeze; warm air temp; lots of black flies; water level 30 cm; encountered sandhill crane near the water level marker in the wetland. It would not leave the area and after a few minutes lowered its neck and spread out it's wings towards the ground and came at me at a steady pace. I took this as notice to leave the area immediately. I believe there is a nest in the wetland area and as such will not return to the wetland so as not to disturb the birds. Since mid-April I've also noticed a significant lack of chorsuing and calling from the wetland. END OF MONITORING
